From 1b5d699bf615eb1fbb64b5eab641e67c05b02394 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 23:39:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 099/174] arm64: mm: free_initmem alignment WARN uses
 MMUPAGE_SIZE
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Same pattern as declare_vma (commit a0dd55b): __init_begin / __init_end
are SEGMENT_ALIGN-aligned (64K) per the linker script, not PAGE_SIZE-
aligned at PGCL=6 (256K).  WARN_ON noisily fires twice during boot
even though the underlying free_reserved_area / vunmap_range
operations work at MMUPAGE granularity and don't require PAGE_SIZE
alignment.

Switch the alignment checks to MMUPAGE_SIZE.  On non-PGCL builds this
is identical to the previous PAGE_SIZE check; under PGCL it stops the
spurious WARN spam during boot.

aarch64 PGCL=6 with this + the prior arm64/declare_vma + mm/ioremap
fixes now boots through to userspace and runs the PGCL basic test
suite to completion (19 passed, 0 failed).  Next blocker: kernel
appears to hang during the next test stage (PGCL stress) — separate
follow-up.

Signed-off-by: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@gmail.com>

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/arm64/mm/init.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/mm/init.c b/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
index 1d1faafc4d8f..4d3cf9b54461 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
@@ -411,8 +411,12 @@ void free_initmem(void)
 	void *lm_init_begin = lm_alias(__init_begin);
 	void *lm_init_end = lm_alias(__init_end);
 
-	WARN_ON(!IS_ALIGNED((unsigned long)lm_init_begin, PAGE_SIZE));
-	WARN_ON(!IS_ALIGNED((unsigned long)lm_init_end, PAGE_SIZE));
+	/* Kernel sections are SEGMENT_ALIGN-aligned (64K) per linker script;
+	 * vmap/page-tables walk at MMUPAGE granularity.  PAGE_SIZE alignment
+	 * is over-strict under page-clustering (PAGE_SIZE up to 1MB).
+	 */
+	WARN_ON(!IS_ALIGNED((unsigned long)lm_init_begin, MMUPAGE_SIZE));
+	WARN_ON(!IS_ALIGNED((unsigned long)lm_init_end, MMUPAGE_SIZE));
 
 	free_reserved_area(lm_init_begin, lm_init_end,
 			   POISON_FREE_INITMEM, "unused kernel");
